.START 

Two General Motors Corp. divisions are expanding consumer incentive programs on certain 1989 and 1990 model autos. 

Chevrolet is broadening its first-time buyer program to offer $600 in down-payment assistance on 1989 and 1990 model Cavaliers, Camaros, Corsicas, Berettas, S-10 pickups and all Geo cars.
Previously, only the 1989 Geos and S-10 pickups were included. 

Chevrolet is also adding $750 rebates on its 1989 model full-size Suburban and Blazer sport utility vehicles. 

The Truck and Bus Group is adding $750 incentives on its 1989 full-size Jimmy and Suburban models.
The group is dropping incentives on the 4-by-4 full-sized Sierra pickup and on any remaining 1988 models. 

